The paper deals with the study of control attacks on elections, which falls under the category of computational social choice (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the use of algorithms to find attacks on elections, which involves the use of data structures (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses complexity-theoretic hardness results, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the modeling and study of multipronged attacks, which involves the use of simulation and modeling techniques (cs.SI).
